const minScoreAfterChange = (nums) => {
    const n = nums.length;
    let first_min = nums[0], second_min = nums[1], last_max = nums[n - 1], second_last_max = nums[n - 2];

    for (let i = 1; i < n - 1; i++) {
        first_min = Math.min(first_min, nums[i]);
        second_min = Math.min(second_min, nums[i + 1]);
        last_max = Math.max(last_max, nums[i]);
        second_last_max = Math.max(second_last_max, nums[i - 1]);
    }

    const low = Math.min(Math.min(first_min, last_max), Math.min(second_min, second_last_max));
    const high = Math.max(Math.max(first_min, last_max), Math.max(second_min, second_last_max));

    return high - low;
}
```

    First, we find the first and second minimum values 'first_min' and 'second_min' and the last and second last max values 'last_max' and 'second_last_max' in the array. Then, we calculate the low score by taking the minimum of the minimum values of both pairs. The high score is calculated by taking the maximum of the maximum values of both pairs. Finally, we return the difference of the high and low scores as the minimal possible score after changing at most two elements in the array.

